HybridHotfix.Notes:
from the hfix completion notes:
To leverage the fix provided : 1) A new DSS needs to be created as below : Owning Ruleset : Pega-IntegrationEngine Purpose : StreamXML/DetectEmptyProperties Value : true
2) After creating the DSS, one among the below two actions to be performed : a) Stream XML rules should be re-generated (using Connector & Metadata Accelerator) b) Stream XML rules (generated before applying the HFix) should be re-saved.

From the 'implementation nodes' on the HFIX item we can see that the following indexes are required:    a. create index pr4_log_rule_usg_dtl_idx1 on pr4_log_rule_usage_details (pxparentruleusagekey, pxassemblycachekey);
b. create index pr_sys_cache_entry_idx1 on pr_sys_cache_entry( pzentrykey, pzcacheconfigid);
c. create index pr4_log_rule_usage_tidx1 on pr4_log_rule_usage(pxsystemnode, pylabel, pxlastuse, pzinskey, pxclassname) ;

Hfix-9426 has a functional dependency on HFix-9428.  Basically HFix-9426 contains the code changes and HFix-9428 contains the rule changes for the manifest feature.  HFix-9428 is installable via update manager.  This hot fix is dependent on HFix-5812 which is also a hybrid hot fix. 

To install
1. Install DL-33663 which contains HFix-9426 and dependent hot fixes via update manager.
2. Shutdown system
3. Add the following database indexes (needed to go along with Hfix-5812):
a. create index pr4_log_rule_usg_dtl_idx1 on pr4_log_rule_usage_details (pxparentruleusagekey, pxassemblycachekey); 
b. create index pr_sys_cache_entry_idx1 on pr_sys_cache_entry( pzentrykey, pzcacheconfigid); 
c. create index pr4_log_rule_usage_tidx1 on pr4_log_rule_usage(pxsystemnode, pylabel, pxlastuse, pzinskey, pxclassname) ; 
4. Start system and import pxHFix-9428.jar

Hfix-9831 has a functional dependency on HFix-9829.  Basically HFix-9831 contains the code changes and HFix-9829 contains the rule changes for the filename feature.  HFix-9831 is installable via update manager.  These hot fixes are functionally dependent on HFix-9426/HFix-9428 which is also a hybrid.  

The recommended approach is to install both the manifest and unique filename features together.  If customer does not have hfix-9426/hfix-9428 already installed on their system they should follow these instructions to install them together:

1. Install DL item which contains HFix-9831 and its dependent hot fixes via update manager. 
2. Shutdown system
3. Add the following database indexes (needed to go along with Hfix-5812):
a. create index pr4_log_rule_usg_dtl_idx1 on pr4_log_rule_usage_details (pxparentruleusagekey, pxassemblycachekey); 
b. create index pr_sys_cache_entry_idx1 on pr_sys_cache_entry( pzentrykey, pzcacheconfigid); 
c. create index pr4_log_rule_usage_tidx1 on pr4_log_rule_usage(pxsystemnode, pylabel, pxlastuse, pzinskey, pxclassname) ; 
4. Start system and import pxHFix-9829.jar.  There is no need to import the pxHfix-9428 as updated versions of those rules are in the new hot fix jar.

If customer already has hfix-9426/9428 installed on their system follow these instructions:
1. Install DL item which contains HFix-9831 and its dependent hot fixes via update manager. 
2. Shutdown system
3.  Start system and import pxHFix-9829.jar
4.  Importing the pxHfix-9829.jar on a system where hfix-9428 is already installed may result in duplicate rules.  Run these deletes to remove duplicate rules if they exist:
delete from pr4_rule_file where pzinsKey = 'RULE-FILE-FORM WEBWB RULE-ADMIN-EXTRACT!HTM #20140603T140312.140 GMT';
delete from pr4_rule where pzinsKey = 'RULE-OBJ-MODEL RULE-ADMIN-EXTRACT PYDEFAULT #20140603T140338.484 GMT';
delete from pr4_rule where pzinsKey = 'RULE-OBJ-VALIDATE RULE-ADMIN-EXTRACT EXTRACTVALIDATE #20140603T140439.630 GMT';
